hus presents a first step towards filling an important gap in our understanding of the meaning of adulthood.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aAdulthood. 0aLife cycle, Human. 0aSocial role. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Children's Studies.2bisacsh1 aBeilharz, Peter, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978085745531440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780857455314423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780857455314/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK